{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-01-add-more-ex-commands/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-01-add-more-ex-commands/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "`pi-vimmode` already has Ex command-line mode, visual range capture, a dedicated Ex render row, literal `:s`/`:substitute`, search highlights, unnamed/named registers, and prompt-buffer line operations. The parser and executor are currently substitution-shaped (`parseExSubstitution` returns only substitution results), so adding more commands should first generalize the Ex parser around a finite `ParsedExCommand` union instead of bolting command branches onto substitution parsing. ## Goals / Non-"}, {"id": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-01-add-more-ex-commands/design.md", "source_location": "line 5", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Add a finite, tested set of prompt-buffer Ex commands: `:delete`/`:d`, `:yank`/`:y`, `:put`/`:pu`, `:copy`/`:t`, `:move`/`:m`, `:join`/`:j`, and `:nohlsearch`/`:noh`."}, {"id": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-01-add-more-ex-commands/design.md", "source_location": "line 20", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "### Generalize parser around `parseExCommand` Replace or wrap `parseExSubstitution` with a parser that returns a discriminated union:"}, {"id": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_generalize_parser_around_parseexcommand", "label": "Generalize parser around parseExCommand", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-01-add-more-ex-commands/design.md", "source_location": "line 22", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Replace or wrap `parseExSubstitution` with a parser that returns a discriminated union: - `empty`"}, {"id": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_keep_ranges_shared_add_destination_parsing_only_for_copy_move", "label": "Keep ranges shared, add destination parsing only for copy/move", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-01-add-more-ex-commands/design.md", "source_location": "line 41", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Use the existing Ex range grammar for command ranges: omitted current line, `%`, visual `'<,'>`, numeric line, `.`, `$`, and comma ranges. Add a separate destination-address parser for `:copy`/`:t` and `:move`/`:m` that accepts `0`, numeric lines, `.`, and `$` as a single insertion target. Destination `0` means before the first line; other destinations mean after the addressed line. Alternative rejected: support destination ranges, visual markers, offsets, or semicolon ranges now. Those expand g"}, {"id": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_implement_line_commands_in_prompt_buffer_helpers", "label": "Implement line commands in prompt-buffer helpers", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-01-add-more-ex-commands/design.md", "source_location": "line 47", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Add buffer helpers that operate on `LineRange` and destination addresses: - delete addressed lines and return a linewise unnamed register payload"}, {"id": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_side_effects_stay_finite_and_visible", "label": "Side effects stay finite and visible", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-01-add-more-ex-commands/design.md", "source_location": "line 62", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- `:delete` writes the deleted linewise text to the unnamed register. - `:yank` writes addressed linewise text to the unnamed register without editing prompt text. - `:put` reads only the unnamed register; missing or empty register is a safe no-op with a readable Ex error."}, {"id": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_status_messages_remain_lightweight", "label": "Status messages remain lightweight", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-01-add-more-ex-commands/design.md", "source_location": "line 73", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Use transient Ex row messages for success and errors: - `N lines deleted`"}, {"id": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_risks_trade_offs", "label": "Risks / Trade-offs", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-01-add-more-ex-commands/design.md", "source_location": "line 88", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- More Ex aliases may look like full Vim parity \u2192 Mitigation: docs and specs list supported aliases exactly and keep unsupported commands as Ex errors. - Destination `0` is destination-only, not a general range address \u2192 Mitigation: parser has separate range and destination functions with tests for `0` rejection in ranges and acceptance in destinations. - Move/copy line math can drift around overlapping ranges \u2192 Mitigation: implement in `src/buffer.ts` with focused unit tests for before, after, "}, {"id": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_migration_plan", "label": "Migration Plan", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-01-add-more-ex-commands/design.md", "source_location": "line 96", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "No data migration. Implement behind existing `:` Ex command-line path. Existing substitution commands remain compatible. Rollback is removing new parser branches and buffer helpers while keeping substitution branch unchanged. ## Open Questions"}, {"id": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_ref_src_buffer_ts", "label": "buffer.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-01-add-more-ex-commands/design.md", "source_location": "line 12", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_ref_src_ex_ts", "label": "ex.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-01-add-more-ex-commands/design.md", "source_location": "line 39", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_ref_src_modal_engine_ts", "label": "engine.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-01-add-more-ex-commands/design.md", "source_location": "line 39", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_document", "target": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_context", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-01-add-more-ex-commands/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_document", "target": "2026_06_01_add_more_ex_commands_design_goals_non_goals", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_fil